FeedbackComment: It is difficult to know what 'without external knowledge' means really. Knowing how a computer works is essential to interpreting a CVE, but does that count as 'external knowledge'? When a CVE talks about being able to trigger something from a log, which is a userland process in Windows, is that external knowledge, or just knowing how computers work? I suspect this will cloud the results of the survey greatly, since different people consider different knowledge 'external' or not.
I was quite surprised to see how critical contextual knowledge of what products are used for which propose is for understanding the impact of CVEs from their textual descriptions.
It would be nice to see some indication of the progress, e.g. 'question 5 out of 25' in the header would be really good.
